On
May
30,
Tograth
disembarked
at
Marseilles.
The
people

were
massed
along
the
quays;
Tograth
landed
from
the
steamer
in

a
launch.
No
sooner
was
he
recognized
than
cries,
shouts,
toasts,

from

the

Tograth,
tall
and
thin,
was
stand

ing
up

launch.
As
it
approached
the
land,
the
features
of
the

hero
could
be
distinguished
more
and
more
clearly.
His
face
was

smooth-shaven
and
blue,
his
mouth
almost
lipless,
disfigured
by
an

ugly
cut;
he
had
a
receding
chin

His
brow
rose
straight
up,
very

high
and
very
large.
Tograth
was
dressed
in
a
pasty
white
costume,

his
shoes
also
being
white
and
high-heeled.
He
wore
no
hat.
As
soon

as
he
placed
his
foot
upon
the
soil
of
Marseilles

furor

Several
men

hero
